The fire broke out at Unit 2 shortly after 09:00 this morning.
The blaze was caused by an oil spill and investigations are ongoing. Duvha spokeswoman Ms Lenny Maseko earlier confirmed the oil spill, but denied the fire. Meanwhile, multiple videos received by www.mobserver.co.za clearly show emergency services battling the blaze, while surrounding buildings were vacated. The extent of the damage is not clear, with Ms Maseko saying all units are operational. 